    public interface RunProfile
    Base interface for things that can be executed (run configurations explicitly managed by user, or custom run profile implementations created from code).
    See Also:
    RunConfiguration, ConfigurationFactory.createTemplateConfiguration(com.intellij.openapi.project.Project)

    • Method Detail

      • getState

        RunProfileState getState(Executor executor,
                         ExecutionEnvironment environment)
                  throws ExecutionException
        Prepares for executing a specific instance of the run configuration.
        Parameters:
        executor - the execution mode selected by the user (run, debug, profile etc.)
        environment - the environment object containing additional settings for executing the configuration.
        Returns:
        the RunProfileState describing the process which is about to be started, or null if it's impossible to start the process.
        Throws:
        ExecutionException

      • getName

        java.lang.String getName()
        Returns the name of the run configuration.
        Returns:
        the name of the run configuration.

      • getIcon

        javax.swing.Icon getIcon()
        Returns the icon for the run configuration. This icon is displayed in the tab showing the results of executing the run profile, and for persistent run configurations is also used in the run configuration management UI.
        Returns:
        the icon for the run configuration, or null if the default executor icon should be used.
